Ullucus tuberosus

   [2120.gif]
   Authority Caldas
   Family Magnoliopsida:Caryophyllidae:Caryophyllales:Basellaceae
   Synonyms Ullucus tuberosus Lozano, Ullucus kunthii Moq., Basella
   tuberosa HBK, Melloca tuberosa Lindl., Melloca peruviana Lindl.
   Common names ulluco, melloco, oca quina, rubas (Ecuador), olloco,
   ulluca, ulluma (Argentina), papa lisas, lisas (Bolivia), olluco,
   papalisa (Peru), rubas, camarones de tierra, ruhuas (Colombia),
   micuche, miguri, ruba, tinquino (Venezuela)
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 2120

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION An erect, compact plant reaching 20-50 cm in height.
   Tuber shapes vary from spherical to cylindrical and colours range from
   white, light green, pink and orange to purple. USES The tuber is used
   in soups, with meat and in salads. Some varieties contain mucilage and
   need to be preboiled before using. It can be stored frozen or dried.
   GROWING PERIOD Grown as an annual, the growing cycle may be as short as
   150 days, but 180-240 days is more common, and at high elevations 270
   days or more is the norm. COMMON NAMES Ullucu, Ulluco, Ulluku, Ullus,
   Ulluma, Melloco, Olluco, Oca quina, Illako, Rubas, Rubia, Ruba,
   Tinquino, Timbos, Micuche, Mucuchi, Michuri, Michirui miguri, Camarones
   de tierra, Ruhuas, Hubas, Chuguas, Chigua, Papa lisas, Lisas, Olloco,
   Ulluca. FURTHER INF Scientific synonyms: U. kunthii, Basella tuberosa,
   Melloca tuberosa, M. peruviana. Ullucu is probably native of the Andean
   Mountains in Peru, Bolivia and northern Argentina. It is best adapted
   to moist conditions. Found at mid to high altitudes up to 4000 m in the
   Andean mountains, and from sea level in temperate climate. Daylengths
   of 10-13.5 hours are normally needed for tuber production, but there
   may, however, be daylength-neutral types. Yields are 5-9 t/ha of
   tubers.

   Sources
   SOURCES (U. tuberosus Caldas)
   Vietmeyer N 1989 pp 105-113 [PHO, RAIN, TEMP, KTMP, LIG, TEXT, FER,
   DRA, PH]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 471 [USE]
   Purseglove J 1974 pp 628 [KTEMP, USE]
   Tindall H 1983 pp 71-72 [TEXT, TEMP, KTMP, PHO]
   Bermejo J 1994 pp 159-161 [USE]

